(DEVNAVIGATOR COMMANDS RUNBOOK) Tj
T* (-----------------------------) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (This file collects the commands we used so far, with short comments, so you can quickly see) Tj
T* (what to run and in what order.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (RECOMMENDED ORDER) Tj
T* (-----------------) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Run these first if you want the safest flow:) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # 1\) Initialize the database and create default templates) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py init-db) Tj
T* (    ) Tj
T* (    # 2\) Extract emails from a local file and save valid results to the database) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py extract-emails --file your_file.txt --store --source manual) Tj
T* (    ) Tj
T* (    # 3\) Check what was saved) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py stats) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py queue --queue all --limit 20) Tj
T* (    ) Tj
T* (    # 4\) Validate a single email manually) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py validate-email --email person@example.com) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (SETUP) Tj
T* (-----) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Optional: create and edit your environment file) Tj
T* (    cp .env.example .env) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Load the database structure and default templates) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py init-db) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Comment:) Tj
T* (Use this once before running extraction, import, or verification commands on a new database.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (DOCKER WORKFLOW) Tj
T* (---------------) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Build the Docker image) Tj
T* (    docker build -t devnavigator .) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Show the CLI help from inside Docker) Tj
T* (    docker run --rm -it -v "$\(pwd\):/workspace" devnavigator) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
