(    python3 devnavigator.py import-contacts --file your_contacts.csv --source csv_upload) Tj
T* (    --consent) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Comment:) Tj
T* (Use this when your file already has columns like email,name,company,country.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (CHECK WHAT WAS SAVED) Tj
T* (--------------------) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Show high-level contact counts) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py stats) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Show the queue with a few rows) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py queue --queue all --limit 20) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Show only contacts ready to send) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py queue --queue ready --limit 20) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Show only contacts needing review) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py queue --queue review --limit 20) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Show only recent contacts) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py queue --queue recent --limit 20 --recent-hours 24) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Comment:) Tj
T* (These commands are the quickest way to confirm extraction/import worked.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (VALIDATE EMAILS) Tj
T* (---------------) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Full validation for one email) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py validate-email --email person@example.com) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Format-only validation if DNS checks are not wanted) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py validate-email --email person@example.com --skip-dns) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Comment:) Tj
T* (Validation checks syntax and, by default, also tries DNS/MX validation when available.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (AUTOMATED SEARCH AND SAVE TO DATABASE) Tj
ET
endstream
